title: Ask HN: What will ChatGPT mean for a mediocre programmer like me?
text:
I'm a mediocre programmer at best, but ChatGPT is highly likely to surpass programming ability for (some) humans.

Scenarios for some programmers:

- No longer in demand (or less demand)

- Data plumbers who simply plug pre-written code together?

- Look elsewhere outside the field for a different role or career path?

Your thoughts?

Show HN: Built an AI search to sift through the noise of AI tools
text: This is a quick attempt at creating a search tool for finding relevant AI tools based on task or job from 1300 tools. Things like "I want to translate an article", "I want to create a workout plan", "I want to create a website" etc .. Feedback is very welcome and appreciated.

Ask HN: It is 2023, how do you build your JavaScript?
text:
There are quite a few different ways to build js out there, including using the tried and trusted Webpack.

Given that we have javascript + modern syntax, typescript, css, things like tailwind, packaging, compressing, react, etc... what is a build people use nowadays?

Just trying to put the feelers out because I feel like I am a couple of years out of date and would hate to just jump on new projects using tools the community is moving away from.
